{
  "id": "smallhold-ryy",
  "title": "Phase 2: Inbound Federation",
  "description": "Implement the shared inbox and handle every inbound ActivityPub activity type required for interoperability. This is the riskiest interop surface — HTTP signature verification, JSON-LD field extraction, and handling implementation-specific quirks from Mastodon, Pleroma, Misskey, GoToSocial, and Lemmy. Get this right before touching the client API.",
  "design": "Use activitypub-federation for inbox dispatch and HTTP sig verification. Mastodon sends Follow object as either object or URI string — handle both. Announce object may be URI to unfetched post — fetch and cache synchronously. Accept Lemmy Page objects without 500 (just ignore). Shared inbox routes to local actors via to/cc fields.",
  "acceptance_criteria": "A Mastodon user can follow a local persona and receive a Follow accepted notification; inbound Create Note creates a remote_posts row and generates a notification if a local actor is mentioned; Delete activities for unknown posts are silently ignored (no 500); Pleroma charset param accepted; all 12 activity types handled without panics",
  "status": "closed",
